The paper discusses the availability of open access articles in various disciplines, which is relevant to the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of a robot to trawl the web for OA full-texts suggests a focus on computer networks and distributed computing (cs.CY), while the comparison of Green and Gold OA may also relate to cryptography (cs.CR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) in terms of the dissemination and impact of research in these fields.
